lay"></div> <main id="page-content"> <div class="ias-push"> <div class="hidden">1218365</div> <div class="ias-push-item"> <script> var gtmData = ""; </script> <div class="adW"> <div class="adC spBg"> <span class="adL">Advertisement</span>   <div class="adA hidden-xs hidden-sm" style='height:250px; width:970px;'> <div id='div-gpt-ad-interestingengineeringcom38210'></div> </div>   <div class="adA hidden-md hidden-lg" style='height:50px; width:320px;'> <div id='div-gpt-ad-interestingengineeringcom34971'></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="content-wrp container row clearfix"> <div class="content-header column-left"> <div class="content-category clearfix"> <div class="category-title-light small pull-left text-uppercase"> <ol class="simple-nav"> <li> <a href="https://interestingengineering.com/science"> <span>Science</span> </a> </li> </ol> <span class="color-science"></span> </div> </div> <h1 class="content-title" data-url="https://interestingengineering.com/nasa-finds-ammonia-linked-mushballs-and-shallow-lightning-on-jupiter" data-id="nasa-finds-ammonia-linked-mushballs-and-shallow-lightning-on-jupiter">NASA Finds Ammonia-Linked &#039;Mushballs&#039; and &#039;Shallow Lightning&#039; on Jupiter</h1> <p class="content-sub-title">NASA's Juno mission just uncovered two exciting new findings about our solar system's largest planet.</p> <div class="content"> <div class="content-tag tag-top border-bottom"> <div class="post-tag"> <a class="clearfix pull-left" href="https://interestingengineering.com/author/fabienne-lang" rel="author"> <img data-pin-nopin="true" src="https://inteng-storage.s3.amazonaws.com/avatars/bs4H99bMLD3P_thumb.jpg" alt="Fabienne Lang" class="hidden-xs img-circle"> </a> <div class="clearfix"> <span>By&nbsp;</span> <a href="https://interestingengineering.com/author/fabienne-lang" rel="author" class="m-0">Fabienne Lang</a> </div> <span>Aug 07, 2020 </span> </div> <div class="content-share"> <div class="jssocials-share jssocials-share-facebook"> <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="https://facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Finterestingengineering.com%2Fnasa-finds-ammonia-linked-mushballs-and-shallow-lightning-on-jupiter" class="jssocials-share-link"> <i class="fa fa-facebook jssocials-share-logo"></i> </a> </div> <div class="jssocials-share jssocials-share-twitter"> <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="https://twitter.com/share?url=https%3A%2F%2Finterestingengineering.com%2Fnasa-finds-ammonia-linked-mushballs-and-shallow-lightning-on-jupiter" class="jssocials-share-link"> <i class="fa fa-twitter jssocials-share-logo"></i> </a> </div> <div class="jssocials-share jssocials-share-linkedin"> <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Finterestingengineering.com%2Fnasa-finds-ammonia-linked-mushballs-and-shallow-lightning-on-jupiter" class="jssocials-share-link"> <i class="fa fa-linkedin jssocials-share-logo"></i> </a> </div> <div class="jssocials-share jssocials-share-reddit"> <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="https://www.reddit.com/submit?url=https%3A%2F%2Finterestingengineering.com%2Fnasa-finds-ammonia-linked-mushballs-and-shallow-lightning-on-jupiter" class="jssocials-share-link"> <i class="fa fa-reddit-alien jssocials-share-logo"></i> </a> </div> </div> </div> <article class="content clearfix"> <div class="content-image"> <picture> <img class="img-responsive" src="https://inteng-storage.s3.amazonaws.com/img/iea/rV6nxnxZOX/sizes/electrical-storms-on-jupiter_resize_md.jpg" alt="NASA Finds Ammonia-Linked &#039;Mushballs&#039; and &#039;Shallow Lightning&#039; on Jupiter"> </picture> <div class="image-info row clearfix"> <span class="pull-left">Electrical storms illustration on Jupiter</span> <span class="pull-right"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">NASA/JPL-Caltech/SwRI/MSSS/Gerald Eichst&auml;dt/Heidi N. Becker/Koji Kuramura</a></span> </div> </div> <div class="content-text clearfix"> <p id="p-0"><a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://interestingengineering.com/nasas-juno-is-in-position-to-jump-jupiters-shadow" target="_blank" rel="dofollow" data-id="embedded internal links" data-type="link" data-url="https://interestingengineering.com/nasas-juno-is-in-position-to-jump-jupiters-shadow">NASA scientists working on the Juno mission</a> at Jupiter are having a field day. They recently discovered two new findings regarding our solar system's largest planet, which further help push forward theories regarding atmospheric dynamics for all of our solar system's planets.&nbsp;</p><p id="p-1"><a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The team discovered</a> a phenomenon called "shallow lightning" on Jupiter, as well as "mushballs" &mdash; all linked to ammonia.</p><p id="p-2">Their findings were published in the journal <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-020-2532-1" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Nature</em></a> on Wednesday.</p><p id="p-3"><strong><a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://interestingengineering.com/the-biggest-volcano-on-jupiters-moon-io-could-soon-erupt" target="_blank" rel="dofollow" data-id="embedded internal links" data-type="link" data-url="https://interestingengineering.com/the-biggest-volcano-on-jupiters-moon-io-could-soon-erupt">SEE ALSO: THE BIGGEST VOLCANO ON JUPITER'S MOON IO COULD SOON ERUPT</a></strong></p><h1 class="content-title" data-url="https://interestingengineering.com/the-biggest-volcano-on-jupiters-moon-io-could-soon-erupt" data-id="the-biggest-volcano-on-jupiters-moon-io-could-soon-erupt">What are these phenomenons?</h1><p id="p-4">Jupiter is home to what NASA scientists call "shallow lightning," which is an unexpected form of electrical discharge. On Earth, lightning is sparked by water clouds, whereas on Jupiter this shallow lightning is brought about through clouds coming from ammonia-based water.&nbsp;</p><p id="p-5">One other new finding the <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/jupiter" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Juno mission</a> discovered was "mushballs." These are "slushy ammonia-rich hailstones," as <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">NASA's statement</a> explains, and originate from violent thunderstorms on Jupiter.&nbsp;</p><div class="embed-ad" id="ad-5"><div class="vad-player"><script type="text/javascript">if(screen.width>1013){var videoScript=document.createElement('script');videoScript.setAttribute('id','8ef5cecd6a3d4c789cc419bac10c84b2'),videoScript.textContent='cnxps.cmd.push(function () { cnxps({ playerId: "98e195e3-9365-4b73-9f85-323744f63bd1"}).render("8ef5cecd6a3d4c789cc419bac10c84b2");});';}else{ var videoScript=document.createElement('script');videoScript.setAttribute('src','https://player.anyclip.com/anyclip-widget/lre-widget/prod/v1/src/lre.js'),videoScript.setAttribute('pubname','interestingengineeringcom'),videoScript.setAttribute('widgetname','001w000001ZTZiS_1505');}var currentScript=document.currentScript||document.scripts[document.scripts.length-1];currentScript.parentNode.insertBefore(videoScript,currentScript.nextSibling);</script></div></div><p id="p-6">What's interesting about these mushballs is that they "kidnap" ammonia and water from the upper atmosphere and bring them down into Jupiter's atmosphere.&nbsp;</p><figure class="image"><picture><img class="img-responsive" src="https://inteng-storage.s3.amazonaws.com/img/iea/rV6nxnxZOX/sizes/pop-up-clouds-jupiter_resize_md.jpg" alt="NASA Finds Ammonia-Linked 'Mushballs' and 'Shallow Lightning' on Jupiter" title="NASA Finds Ammonia-Linked 'Mushballs' and 'Shallow Lightning' on Jupiter" data-pin-nopin="true"></picture><figcaption>Snapped by the JunoCam, these clouds are thought to be the tops of violent thunderstorms on Jupiter,&nbsp;<em>Source</em>: <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>NASA/JPL-Caltech/SwRI/MSSS/Kevin M. Gill</em></a></figcaption></figure><p id="p-7">These discoveries open up new information about the planet as until now it was thought that these thunderstorms originated from water, and not ammonia.&nbsp;</p><p id="p-8">"<span>Juno's close flybys of the cloud tops allowed us to see something surprising &ndash; smaller, shallower flashes &ndash; originating at much higher altitudes in Jupiter's atmosphere than previously assumed possible," said <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Heidi Becker</a>, Juno's Radiation Monitoring Investigation lead at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory in Southern California and the lead author of the Nature paper.</span></p><p id="p-9"><span>Becker's team discovered that the planet's thunderstorms push water-ice crystals high up into the its atmosphere, and there they encounter atmospheric ammonia vapor that in turn melts the ice. This forms a new ammonia-water solution.&nbsp;</span></p><div class="embed-ad" id="ad-9"><div class="adW b-margin-20 visible-xs visible-sm"><div class="adC spBg"><span class="adL">Advertisement</span><div class="adA" id="div-gpt-ad-interestingengineeringcom38215" style="height:280px; width:336px;"></div></div></div></div><p id="p-10"><span>"At these altitudes, the ammonia acts like an antifreeze, lowering the melting point of water ice and allowing the formation of a cloud with ammonia-water liquid," explained Becker. </span></p><p id="p-11"><span>"In this new state, falling droplets of ammonia-water liquid can collide with the upgoing water-ice crystals and electrify the clouds. This was a big surprise, as ammonia-water clouds do not exist on Earth."</span></p><figure class="image"><picture><img class="img-responsive" src="https://inteng-storage.s3.amazonaws.com/img/iea/rV6nxnxZOX/sizes/graphic-explanation_resize_md.jpg" alt="NASA Finds Ammonia-Linked 'Mushballs' and 'Shallow Lightning' on Jupiter" title="NASA Finds Ammonia-Linked 'Mushballs' and 'Shallow Lightning' on Jupiter" data-pin-nopin="true"></picture><figcaption>Graphic explaining the evolutionary process of "shallow lightning" and "mushballs." <em>Source</em>: <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>NASA/JPL-Caltech/SwRI/CNRS</em></a></figcaption></figure><p id="p-12"><span>Combining their newfound knowledge of both the shallow lightning and mushballs enabled the NASA team to solve Jupiter's ammonia mystery. "As it turned out, the ammonia isn't actually missing; it is just transported down while in disguise, having cloaked itself by mixing with water," explained <a class="underline border-color-science" href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/shallow-lightning-and-mushballs-reveal-ammonia-to-nasas-juno-scientists" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Scott Bolton</a>,&nbsp;Juno's principal investigator at the Southwest Research Institute in San Antonio.</span></p><p id="p-13"><span>"The solution is very simple and elegant with this theory: When the water and ammonia are in a liquid state, they are invisible to us until they reach a depth where they evaporate &ndash; and that is quite deep."</span></p><div class="embed-ad" id="ad-13"><div class="adW b-margin-20 visible-xs visible-sm"><div class="adC spBg"><span class="adL">Advertisement</span><div class="adA" id="div-gpt-ad-interestingengineeringcom38216" style="height:280px; width:336px;"></div></div></div></div><p id="p-14"><span>Another piece of Jupiter's puzzle has been solved, which will open up more doors to new theories surrounding atmospheric dynamics.&nbsp;</span></p><p id="p-15"><span><span class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/tq_6DClZ0Ns?list=PLTiv_XWHnOZpM1iLQr95P4KDXYiYnJUOE" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" class="embed-responsive-item"></iframe></span></span></p> </div> </article> </div> <div class="clearfix"> <div class="adW hidden-xs hidden-sm"> <div class="adC spBg"> <span class="adL">Advertisement</span>   <div class="adA" style='min-width: 300px; display:flex; justify-content: center; align-items:center;'> <div id='div-gpt-ad-interestingengineeringcom38222'></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="news-icon"> <div class="news-container"> <span>Follow Us on</span> <div class="news-button-container"> <div class="google-news"> <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="https://news.google.com/u/1/publications/CAAqBwgKMMualAsw2MapAw"></a> </div> <div class="news-break"> <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="https://www.newsbreak.com/@c/512488"></a> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="container-fluid slim-subscription"> <div class="form-wrapper"> <form method="POST" action="https://interestingengineering.com/subscription" accept-charset="UTF-8" class="subscription sbs-form small-box text-center" style="width:100%;"><input name="_token" type="hidden" value="dmLxT2dX1UxSyJmkHBmPdMDHOnLVlBI78bBMkkhA"> <div class="clearfix"> <div class="clearfix b-margin-20"> <h2>Stay on top of the latest engineering news</h2> <span>Just enter your email and we’ll take care of the rest:</span> </div> <div class="clearfix b-margin-10"> <div class="frm"> <div class="input-group"> <input class="form-control" placeholder="Enter your email address" name="email" type="email"> </div> <button type="submit" class="btn btn-info">SUBSCRIBE</button> <